MEAN is a free and open-source JavaScript software stack for building dynamic web sites and web applications. 
The MEAN stack is MongoDB, Express.js, AngularJS, and Node.js.
The MERN is also similar to MEAN stack except the Angular.js is replaced by React.js.

Node.js is a server side JavaScript execution environment. It’s a platform built on Google Chrome’s V8 JavaScript runtime.

Express is lightweight framework used to build web applications in Node.

MongoDB is a NoSQL database system. MongoDB saves data in binary JSON format which makes it easier to pass data between client and server.

AngularJS is a JavaScript-based open-source front-end web application framework mainly maintained by Google

React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It is maintained by Facebook
